remarks.format:
## Remarks

`SKWebpEncoder` is a static class that encodes single frames and multi-frame animated WebP
images. Pass an <xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderOptions> value to control the compression mode
(lossy or lossless) and quality level.

For single-frame encoding, use one of the `Encode` overloads. For animated WebP, use one of
the `EncodeAnimated` overloads, passing a span of <xref:SkiaSharp.SKWebpEncoderFrame> values.

## Examples

```csharp
using var bitmap = SKBitmap.Decode("photo.png");
using var pixmap = bitmap.PeekPixels();
var options = new SKWebpEncoderOptions(SKWebpEncoderCompression.Lossy, 85);
using var data = SKWebpEncoder.Encode(pixmap, options);
if (data is not null)
    File.WriteAllBytes("photo.webp", data.ToArray());
```
